<div class="text-center text_color d-flex flex-column mt-5 pt-5">
  
  <span class="background-image d-none d-sm-block"></span>
  <h1 class="one-liner">Discover & Catalogue all in one tab.</h1>

  <% if current_user == nil %>
    <%= link_to new_user_session_path do %>
      <button class="btn btn-dark btn-lg mt-5">Get started</button>
    <% end %>
  <% else %>
    <%= link_to search_path do %>
      <button class="btn btn-dark btn-lg mt-5">Get started</button>
    <% end %>
  <% end %>

  <div style="margin-top:425px;">
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-dark mb-5" data-bs-toggle="modal" data-bs-target="#exampleNoteModal">
      Here's an example of a note!
    </button>
  </div>

  <div class="modal fade" id="exampleNoteModal" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="exampleNoteModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-xl">
      <div class="modal-content">
        <div class="modal-header secondary">
          <h1 class="modal-title fs-5" id="exampleNoteModalLabel">Click the game title to minimize the sidebar!</h1>
          <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
        </div>
        <div class="modal-body background">
          <%= render "notes/note", note: @note %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>


  <div class="d-flex justify-content-around accent border rounded features pt-3 container", style="line-height:3;">
    <ul>
      <h3>Discover</h3>
      <span class="text-start">
        <li>
          <p>Search through a vast database of games, courtesy of <%= link_to("Giant Bomb", "https://www.giantbomb.com/") %></p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Input a year at the top of the page to conduct a search, which will display 3 random games from the given year</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Games will be displayed with their title, an image (if available), the platforms they're available on, as well as a short description (if available)</p>
        </li>
      </span>
    </ul>

    <ul>
      <h3>Catalogue</h3>
      <span class="text-start">
        <li>
          <p>Once you find a game you're interested in, you can create a Note based off of it, saving all the sample data for easy access</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Notes can be as simple as you like; use them to jot down your thoughts, or to contain handy links and images</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>Notes can be viewed and edited from your notebook, linked at the top of the page</p>
        </li>
      </span>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
